ce:section.ce:para:
Quantum yield for as-prepared co-doped N, S-CDs was determined by relating the optical densities (OD) and integrated PL intensities (IA) of as-prepared material with quinine sulphate (Φ=0.54) in 0.1 M H2SO4 as the reference standard. UV-3600 (Shimadzu, Japan) absorption spectrophotometer was used to determine the OD (absorbance) at 350 nm. The fluorescence emission spectral studies had been analyzed through excitation of 350 nm by using an LS-45 Fluorescent Spectrometer (Perkin Elmer). Five concentrations were made for the determination of quantum yield, all the concentrations had absorbance less than 0.1 at 350 nm. By plotting the integrated fluorescence intensity against the optical density value and using the following Eq. (1) the quantum yield of the as-prepared N, S-CDs was calculated as;
(1) ɸ = QRef × (IASam / IARef) × (ODRef / ODSam) × (η2 Sam / η 2 Ref) →
where, ɸ is the quantum yield of N, S-CDs, η represents refractive index, QR corresponds to the quantum yield of reference (quinine sulfate), IASam and IARef is the integral area of standard and sample, ODRef and ODSam are optical density of standard and probe respectively.
